---
const contact = "hello@desciencemodel.com";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <meta name="generator" content={Astro.generator} />
    <title>de science model</title>
    <meta name="description" content="Building a new knowledge representation format and world model for scientific knowledge." />
    <meta name="robots" content="noindex, nofollow" />
    <link rel="icon" href="/favicon.svg" type="image/svg+xml" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.bunny.net" />
    <link href="https://fonts.bunny.net/css?family=eb-garamond:400,400i,600|instrument-sans:400,400i,500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
    <style>
      *, *::before, *::after {
        box-sizing: border-box;
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
      }

      :root {
        --bg: #f4f1eb;
        --ink: #1c1a17;
        --ink-muted: #6b6457;
        --serif: "EB Garamond", Georgia, serif;
        --sans: "Instrument Sans", system-ui, sans-serif;
      }

      html {
        background: var(--bg);
        color: var(--ink);
        font-family: var(--sans);
        font-size: 17px;
        line-height: 1.6;
        -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
      }

      body {
        min-height: 100dvh;
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
      }

      main {
        flex: 1;
        max-width: 660px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 0 2rem;
        padding-top: clamp(4rem, 12vh, 8rem);
        padding-bottom: 6rem;
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 3rem;
      }

      .wordmark {
        font-family: var(--sans);
        font-size: 0.78rem;
        font-weight: 500;
        letter-spacing: 0.12em;
        text-transform: lowercase;
        color: var(--ink-muted);
      }

      .hero {
        margin-top: 1rem;
      }

      h1 {
        font-family: var(--serif);
        font-size: clamp(1.9rem, 4.5vw, 2.6rem);
        font-weight: 400;
        line-height: 1.25;
        color: var(--ink);
        letter-spacing: -0.01em;
      }

      h1 em {
        font-style: italic;
      }

      .body {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 1.2rem;
      }

      .body p {
        font-size: 1rem;
        line-height: 1.7;
        color: var(--ink);
        max-width: 54ch;
      }

      .body p + p {
        color: var(--ink-muted);
      }

      .divider {
        width: 2rem;
        height: 1px;
        background: var(--ink-muted);
        opacity: 0.35;
      }

      .contact {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 0.5rem;
      }

      .contact-label {
        font-size: 0.78rem;
        letter-spacing: 0.08em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--ink-muted);
      }

      .contact a {
        font-family: var(--sans);
        font-size: 0.95rem;
        color: var(--ink);
        text-decoration: underline;
        text-underline-offset: 3px;
        text-decoration-color: var(--ink-muted);
        transition: text-decoration-color 0.15s;
      }

      .contact a:hover {
        text-decoration-color: var(--ink);
      }

      footer {
        padding: 2rem;
        text-align: center;
        font-size: 0.75rem;
        color: var(--ink-muted);
        opacity: 0.5;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <main>
      <span class="wordmark">das model</span>

      <section class="hero">
        <h1>
          The scientific paper was<br />
          designed for the printing press.<br />
          <em>Science has outgrown it.</em>
        </h1>
      </section>

      <div class="divider" aria-hidden="true"></div>

      <section class="body">
        <p>
          Papers fix knowledge in amber — linear, static, author-bound.
          The paper paradigm is <a class="conact" href=https://carlaostmann.substack.com/p/papers-block-scientific-progress target="_blank">over.</a>
          They cannot represent the structure beneath a result: the competing
          hypotheses, the weight of evidence, the provenance of a claim,
          the conditions under which something is true, the entities and substances involved.
        </p>
        <p>
          We're building a knowledge representation format and world model
          for science. Not a better document. A different primitive entirely.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="contact">
        <span class="contact-label">Get in touch</span>
        <a href={`mailto:${contact}`}>{contact}</a>
      </section>
    </main>

    <footer>stealth · {new Date().getFullYear()}</footer>
  </body>
</html>
